Fish - Set Variable

Use the [prgm]set[/prgm] command in fish to set, or clear, a variable.

# Set persistent variables
$ [prgm]set[/prgm] [arg]--universal[/arg]  # --universal immediately available to all fish instances

# Set Transient variables
$ [prgm]set[/prgm] [arg]-g[/arg]  # --global - visible to all functions in the shell
$ [prgm]set[/prgm] [arg]-x[/arg]  # --export - visible to child-processes

# Check if a variable is set
$ [prgm]set[/prgm] [arg]-q[/arg]  # --query
